# ğŸ§  JavaScript Variables â€“ Complete Notes + Code

---

## âœ… What is a Variable?

A **variable** is like a **container** that stores a value in memory so you can reuse it later.

```js
let age = 25;
let name = "Venky";
```

---

## âœ… 1. Declaration and Initialization

### ğŸ‘‰ Declaration

Declaring a variable means **creating** it:

```js
let x; // declared but undefined
```

### ğŸ‘‰ Initialization

Giving it a **value**:

```js
x = 10; // now initialized
```

### Combined:

```js
let y = 20; // declared + initialized
```

---

## âœ… 2. Types of Variable Declarations

| Keyword | Reassignable? | Redeclarable? | Block Scoped?         | Hoisted?          |
| ------- | ------------- | ------------- | --------------------- | ----------------- |
| `var`   | âœ… Yes         | âœ… Yes         | âŒ No (function scope) | âœ… Yes (undefined) |
| `let`   | âœ… Yes         | âŒ No          | âœ… Yes                 | âœ… Yes (TDZ)       |
| `const` | âŒ No          | âŒ No          | âœ… Yes                 | âœ… Yes (TDZ)       |

---

## ğŸŸ¡ `var` â€“ Function Scoped (Old Style)

```js
var a = 10;
var a = 20; // Redeclaration allowed
a = 30;     // Reassignment allowed

function testVar() {
  var inside = "I'm inside function";
  console.log(inside);
}
// console.log(inside); âŒ Error: not accessible outside
```

---

## ğŸŸ¢ `let` â€“ Block Scoped (Modern and Recommended)

```js
let b = 100;
// let b = 200; âŒ Error: can't redeclare
b = 150; // âœ… allowed

if (true) {
  let temp = "Only in block";
  console.log(temp);
}
// console.log(temp); âŒ Error
```

---

## ğŸ”´ `const` â€“ Block Scoped Constant

```js
const pi = 3.14;
// pi = 3.1415; âŒ Error: cannot reassign

const person = { name: "Venky" };
person.name = "Venkat"; // âœ… Allowed: object is not frozen
```

> `const` means the **reference** can't change, not the content.

---

## ğŸ§  Hoisting in Variables

| Keyword         | Behavior                                    |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `var`           | Hoisted as `undefined`                      |
| `let` / `const` | Hoisted but in **Temporal Dead Zone** (TDZ) |

```js
console.log(x); // undefined
var x = 10;

console.log(y); // âŒ Error
let y = 20;
```

---

## ğŸ¯ Naming Rules (Identifiers)

âœ… Valid:

```js
let name;
let _score;
let $price;
let user1;
```

âŒ Invalid:

```js
// let 1user;
// let var;
// let full-name;
```

---

## ğŸ§© Dynamic Typing

JavaScript is **dynamically typed**. Variable types can change.

```js
let data = 10;
data = "Now a string";
data = true;
```

---

## ğŸ§ª Example: Using All Variables Together

```js
var count = 5;
let name = "Venky";
const gravity = 9.8;

console.log("Count:", count);
console.log("Name:", name);
console.log("Gravity:", gravity);

name = "Venkat"; // âœ…
count = 10;      // âœ…
```

---

## ğŸ§  Interview Tip: const with arrays/objects

```js
const arr = [1, 2];
arr.push(3); // âœ… allowed
// arr = [1, 2, 3]; âŒ not allowed

const obj = { name: "Venky" };
obj.name = "V"; // âœ… allowed
```

---

## âœ… Summary

| Feature      | `var`           | `let`           | `const`         |
| ------------ | --------------- | --------------- | --------------- |
| Scope        | Function        | Block           | Block           |
| Reassignable | âœ…               | âœ…               | âŒ               |
| Redeclarable | âœ…               | âŒ               | âŒ               |
| Hoisting     | Yes (undefined) | Yes (TDZ error) | Yes (TDZ error) |
| Use for      | Legacy code     | Most variables  | Constants       |

---

## ğŸ”¥ Real-Life Analogy

* `var` = old storage room â†’ things leak outside
* `let` = labeled box with flexibility
* `const` = sealed box â†’ content can shift inside but box can't be replaced

